                <mxCell id="379" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2. when we convert any binary to octal or hex&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;via grouping, then at that time&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;why don&#39;t we pad required zero at right instead&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;pad zero at left ?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Becuase padding the Zero at the LSB(right) will&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;completely change the meaning of that byte,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;while padding at MSB keeps the value/meaning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 19px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;of that byte same&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;h